value.title: Congressman suggests street violence after judge rejects bid to force Pence to block Biden win
value.excerpt: Texas congressman Louie Gohmert suggested that 'violence in the streets' may be the only remaining option to block Joe Biden from becoming president.

value.title: Texas’ Ted Cruz Leads 11 Senators in Attempt to Challenge Joe Biden’s Victory
value.excerpt: Texas Sen. Ted Cruz said he will spearhead a drive by nearly a dozen Republican senators to challenge President-elect Joe Biden’s victory in the Senate.

value.title: Eric Trump, Don Jr. party with Vanilla Ice at Mar-a-Lago New Year’s bash
value.excerpt: President Trump skipped out on performances by ’90s pop-rapper Vanilla Ice, Beach Boys founder Mike Love and other throwback acts at a pricey Mar-a-Lago New Year’s Eve bash.

value.title: On the anniversary eve of the drone strike ordered by Trump that killed its top general, Iran reveals its plan to enrich uranium to 20% purity
value.excerpt: "We are like soldiers and our fingers are on the triggers," the head of Iran's civilian atomic energy organization said.

value.title: Iran foreign minister warns Trump 'fireworks will backfire,' as tensions escalate
value.excerpt: Amid heightened tensions between the U.S. and Iran, Iranian Foreign Minister Javad Zarif on Saturday warned President Trump that any "fireworks would backfire."

value.title: A former Blackwater contractor pardoned by Trump said he 'acted correctly' and feels at 'peace' for his role in death of 14 Iraqi civilians
value.excerpt: In an Associated Press interview, Evan Liberty showed little remorse for his role in the 2007 Baghdad shooting that killed 14 Iraqi civilians.

value.title: Iran's foreign minister urges Trump to avoid Israel "trap" to provoke war
value.excerpt: Iranian Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif urged U.S. President Donald Trump on Saturday not to be "trapped" by an alleged Israeli plan to provoke a war through attacks on U.S. forces in Iraq.

value.title: Analysis: How Trump made people care about politics again
value.excerpt: Love him or hate him, President Donald Trump made most Americans feel strongly about politics in a way no politician has in our lifetimes. value.title: China has accused Trump of trying to start a new Cold War, after the New York Stock Exchange confirmed plan to delist three Chinese firms
value.excerpt: China accused the Trump administration of attempting to suppress foreign companies, as the NYSE moved to delist three Chinese firms.

value.title: Pro-Trump lawyer Lin Wood insists he is not insane after tweeting that Mike Pence should face execution by firing squad
value.excerpt: In a Twitter thread, the conservative lawyer and staunch Trump ally accused senior Republicans of helping to "steal" the election.

value.title: Trump the clear Republican 'front-runner' in next White House race
value.excerpt: There's more than three years to go until the next Iowa caucuses and New Hampshire presidential primary, but what some considered the first cattle call in the 2024 White House race takes place next week.

value.title: Trump and Hawley set off Republican meltdown with Georgia elections looming
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump is stoking division in the Republican ranks days before control of the Senate -- and the balance of power in Washington -- is decided in a pair of runoff elections in Georgia.

value.title: Federal judge throws out Gohmert lawsuit asking Pence to interfere in Electoral College count
value.excerpt: A federal judge threw out a lawsuit from Rep. Louie Gohmert of Texas and several Arizona Republicans seeking to force Vice President Mike Pence to help throw the election to President Donald Trump next week when Congress meets to count the Electoral College votes.

value.title: 'Lack standing': Rep. Gohmert's lawsuit against Pence to overturn election results thrown out
value.excerpt: U.S. District Court Judge Jeremy Kernodle, a Trump appointee, said Rep. Louie Gohmert and a group of other Republicans on the lawsuit "lack standing."

value.title: Congress overrode Trump’s veto. The president’s response? ‘Pathetic!!!’
value.excerpt: Congress has overridden President Donald Trump’s veto of a defense policy bill, a first by lawmakers since he took office.

value.title: Trump vetoes Calif. fishing bill over seafood trade deficit
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has vetoed a bill that would have gradually ended the use of large-mesh drift gillnets used exclusively in federal waters off the coast of California

value.title: President Trump says South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem should challenge 'RINO' Sen. John Thune in 2022
value.excerpt: Thune drew Trump’s ire in recent days after he criticized the president’s bid to challenge the results of the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Mike Pence seeks dismissal of lawsuit aiming to give him the power to overturn election loss
value.excerpt: The Justice Department has asked to dismiss a lawsuit led by a House Republican that seeks to give Mike Pence power to overturn the election.

value.title: What Will Pence Do When Congress Counts the Votes?
value.excerpt: Readers are shocked that the question is being asked and speculate that the vice president may find an excuse not to be present. They also criticize Senator Josh Hawley.

value.title: Mike Pence heading to Georgia on Monday ahead of runoff elections
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is heading to Georgia on Monday to campaign ahead of Tuesday’s critical U.S. Senate runoff elections.

value.title: Fact check: President Trump spent Thanksgiving with troops in Afghanistan in 2019, not 2020
value.excerpt: Social media users having been sharing posts that claim President Donald Trump spent Thanksgiving 2020 with troops in Bagram, Afghanistan, not playing golf. This claim is false: the photo of Trump in Bagram is from 2019.

value.title: 'Dangerous ploy': GOP Sen. Ben Sasse slams efforts by Trump, Hawley to overturn election
value.excerpt: Nebraska Republican Sen. Ben Sasse denounced the "institutional arsonist members of Congress who will object to the Electoral College vote."

value.title: Joe Biden, Nancy Pelosi to Draw on Their History in Bid to Unite Fractious Democrats
value.excerpt: The president-elect and House speaker share the job of steering a divided Democratic coalition amid a pandemic and an economy recovering from a deep slump.

value.title: Trump attacks and vote by mail: the top voting rights stories of 2020
value.excerpt: The pandemic created new barriers to the ballot box and strengthened existing ones – aided by the president and his Republican allies
